text: Their offering last night differed little from their earlier act on this show a week or so ago. But the Mudlarks, with Jeff Mudd out of the Army and back with sister Mary and brother Fred, were in bright, zestful form. Why only two numbers, though? It was not enough. "A FAIR COP," the B B C Whitehall farce last night, looked like a rabbit warren in a field of corn.
